x4freetext: Thin foils of isotopically pure (> 99 %) metal. Some
were made self-supporting while others were mounted
on thin (20 mu- g/cm2) carbon backings. The target
thicknesses ranged from 50 mu-g/cm2 to 700 mu-g/cm2,
depending on the material and method of manufacture.
mounted in a 38 cm vertical scattering chamber.
To enable forward-angle measurements to be
taken, use was made of the Browne-Buechner type
The forward-angle inelastic scattering data was
collected using the spectrometer with a solid-state
position sensitive detector mounted in its focal plane
